title: Tax returns of Donald Trump
deleted: Several states have proposed bills that would require presidential candidates to release their tax returns in order to be listed on the presidential ballots, including [[California]] and [[New York (state)|New York]], for the [[2020 United States presidential election|2020 ballot]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.politico.com/states/california/story/2019/07/30/californias-newsom-signs-bill-to-force-trump-tax-returns-1122154|title=California's Newsom signs bill to force Trump tax returns|last=White|first=Jeremy|date=July 30, 2019|work=Politico|access-date=August 5, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2019/11/22/trump-tax-returns-safe-after-california-court-ruling-on-primary.html|title=California high court tosses law aimed at forcing Trump to release tax returns to get on state primary ballot|date=July 30, 2019|work=CNBC|access-date=April 20, 2020}}</ref> <ref name="McKinley2019">{{cite news|last1=McKinley|first1=Jesse|last2=Fandos|first2=Nicholas|title=Cuomo Signs a Bill to Allow Release of Trump's State Tax Returns|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/07/08/nyregion/trump-ny-taxes-cuomo.html|work=The New York Times|date=July 8, 2019}}</ref>
